description:
Truly, you will not find a dumber hour of sketch comedy in all of dirty old New York City.

Two great shows together at last!

1. FAMBLY'S RUSTY BUCKET:

With everything going on in the news today, Fambly brings to you a show that addresses none of it. In "Fambly's Rusty Bucket," this New York Times acclaimed sketch group will be hitting none of the major issues. There will be no topical sketches, and no theme. Guaranteed.

Starring: Veronica Osorio, Dan Black, Dan Chamberlain, Nicole Beyer, Mamrie Hart, and Zach Broussard

Written by: Madalyn Baldanzi, Jason Shebiro, Kathy Salerno, Colin Elzie, Pat O'Brien, and Ben Wietmarschen

Directed by Dan Mirk

2. THE HONEYMEN PRESENT: A SALUTE TO HONEY

The Honeymen are three dapper song-and-dance men who love nothing more than the sweet taste of honey. With help from the Honeyplayers, they're putting on a all-star variety show like no other extolling the virtues of that sticky-sweet treat that's fun to eat. The only ones who could possibly stop them are their sworn enemies, the dastardly Mustard Brothers.

Written by and starring Colin Elzie, Pat O'Brien, and Ben Wietmarschen

With Dan Chamberlain, Mamrie Hart, Dave Bluvband, Zack Poitras, and Eric Gersen on Piano.

Special shirtless video appearance by Arthur Meyer

Directed by Zack Poitras

Make Reservations Here (this show is $5): http://newyork.ucbtheatre.com/shows/view/3206
